def plot_heatmap(from_station, time_lower, time_upper, agg_col, fmt, operator = 'LM'):
    
    metrics = {
                'minutes_late' : 'Avg. minutes late',
                'on_time' : 'Percentage of trains on time',
                'cancelled' : 'Percentage of trians cancelled'
              }
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize = (15,15))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    
    _ = sns.heatmap(df.loc[(df.operator == operator) & \
                           (df.from_station == from_station) & \
                           (df.scheduled_depart > pd.to_datetime(time_lower).time()) & \
                           (df.scheduled_depart < pd.to_datetime(time_upper).time())].pivot_table(values  = agg_col,
                                                                                                  index   = 'scheduled_depart',
                                                                                                  columns = 'day_name')[['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday']].dropna(),
        annot = True,
        cmap  = 'YlOrRd',
        alpha = .5,
        fmt   = fmt,
        linecolor = None,
        square = True,
        cbar = False,
        ax = ax
    )
    
    cbar = ax.figure.colorbar(ax.collections[0])
    #cbar.set_label('Avg. mins late', color = TICK_COLOURS, size = '12')
    for l in cbar.ax.yaxis.get_ticklabels():
        l.set_color(TICK_COLOURS)
        
    plt.title('Operator: {}\nDeparting from: {}\nMetric: {}'.format(operator, from_station, metrics[agg_col]), color = TICK_COLOURS, size = 15)
    ax.tick_params(colors = TICK_COLOURS, labelsize = 12)
    ax.set_xlabel('Day of week', color = TICK_COLOURS, size = 12)
    ax.set_ylabel('Train departure', color = TICK_COLOURS, size = 12)
    
    ax.plot()

def rolling_plot(from_station, time_lower, time_upper, windows, operator = 'LM', days = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday']):
    
    cols = ['minutes_late', 'cancelled', 'on_time']
    df2 = df.loc[(df.operator == 'LM') & \
                 (df.from_station == from_station) & \
                 (df.scheduled_depart > pd.to_datetime(time_lower).time()) & \
                 (df.scheduled_depart < pd.to_datetime(time_upper).time()) & \
                 (df.day_name.isin(days))].groupby('date_')[cols].agg(['sum', 'count'])
    
    df2.columns = ['_'.join(col).strip() for col in df2.columns.values]
    df2.reset_index(inplace=True)

    cols_agg = [a+b for a,b in itertools.product(cols,['_sum', '_count'])]
    
    for w in windows:
        df2[[x + '_roll' + str(w) for x in cols_agg]] = df2[cols_agg].rolling(window = w, center = False).sum()

    r_upper = len(df2.columns)/2 + .5
    calc_cols = [[df2.columns[2*i-1], df2.columns[2*i]] for i in range(1,int(r_upper))]

    for col_pair in calc_cols:
        field_part   = re.sub('(\_roll[0-9]+)', '', col_pair[0])[:-4]
        rolling_part = re.sub('[^0-9]', '', col_pair[0])

        df2[field_part + '_avg' + rolling_part] = df2[col_pair[0]] / df2[col_pair[1]]
        df2.drop(col_pair, axis = 1, inplace = True)

    df2.set_index('date_', inplace=True)
    
    df2[[x for x in df2.columns if 'minutes_late' in x]].plot(figsize=(20,10), alpha = .5)
    plt.title('Operator: {}\nDeparting from: {}\nMetric: {}'.format(operator, from_station, 'Average minutes late'), color = TICK_COLOURS, size = 15)
    
    df2[[x for x in df2.columns if 'canc' in x]].plot(figsize=(20,10), alpha = .5)
    plt.title('Operator: {}\nDeparting from: {}\nMetric: {}'.format(operator, from_station, 'Cancellation rate'), color = TICK_COLOURS, size = 15)
    
    df2[[x for x in df2.columns if 'time' in x]].plot(figsize=(20,10), alpha = .5)
    plt.title('Operator: {}\nDeparting from: {}\nMetric: {}'.format(operator, from_station, 'Percentage on time'), color = TICK_COLOURS, size = 15)
